entry.note: Do NOT translate 'timetable' and 'isregular': they are class and function names

message.entry: Input timetable must be regular with respect to absolute time, or a time unit supported by isregular. For details, see isregular.
Input timetable must be regular with respect to {0}.
Lag interval must be a scalar integer, duration, or calendarDuration.
Lag interval must be a multiple of input timetable's time step. Use RETIME to interpolate timetable variables at times that fall between the row times.
Lag interval for timetable with duration row times must be a scalar integer or duration.
calendarDuration lag interval must be an integer multiple of either calendar months, calendar days, or time.
